The passion for Bauer's portraits led him to repeat the idea two years ago with the "Portraits of old sportsmen" ("SportARTproject").
Although the concepts are different in "Flamenco - people", the photographer admits that he loves photographing the portrait of people, knowing them and being able to enter their lives for a moment more or less long.
I believe that in photography the portrait is the most difficult genre.
You're in front of people, characters that sometimes you don't know or that just leave you a few minutes to take a picture of them.
Despite these circumstances, as a photographer, I always try to make my ideas reality."
This collection of portraits of the current flamenco called "Flamenco - people", is exhibited at the El Fotómata Gallery, located at number 20 on the rue de la Mata (a parallel street to the People of Hercules) which will be open until October 16th.
