Monday, the House of Representatives will be the first to vote on the bill on behalf of the emergency economic stabilization law of 2008. Then it will be in the hands of the Senate.
On Saturday evening, President George W. Bush spoke to Pelosi, and then the White House also welcomed the news of the agreement.
"We are pleased with the progress made this night, and we strongly appreciate the efforts of both parties to stabilize our financial markets and protect our economy" - said Tony Fratto, spokesman for the White House.
Furthermore, the diverging programme of the Bush administration's initial proposal, which mentioned that the $700 billion needed to be spent at one time, was to be used for the buy-back of suspicious credit securities.
From now on, a maximum of half of the sum of 700 billion can be spent. The first 250 billion will be issued immediately after the adoption of the law by Congress, probably on Monday. This first amount will be used by the Treasury to buy suspicious bank receivables, while the use of the additional $100 billion will be left to the President's discretion.
The program will be supervised by an independent body, in which the President of the Federal Reserve will also participate.
The expenditure of the second half of the 700 billion depends on a new Congress decree.
Under the Act, the Treasury secretariat will be able to implement a combined strategy: at the same time, it will be able to purchase suspicious receivables, suspicious mortgages and mortgages, as well as other types of "toxic" receivables.
Competent persons in the department stated that buy-backs may take place as part of an auction, but also directly.
The rule allows the companies concerned to participate in an insurance program, where the Treasury secretariat guarantees the tools that cause concern, for which companies have paid a premium equivalent to foreseeable damages.
Henry Paulson stated that the law provides the necessary tools to provide $700 billion for the urgent needs of the financial system, whether it involves the extensive redemption of suspicious debts, their insurance, or the risk of seeing the system collapse from one major financial institution or another.
"We will take the necessary steps to be ready to apply the law as soon as it is signed" - he added.
On the other hand, bank leaders in bad positions and waiting for state aid can expect their retirement benefits, simply called gold parachute overseas, to be capped by the government.
The cap on wages is only mentioned in specific cases, and the limitations depend on how the Treasury secretariat proposes its support to the company.
The cap principle means that if the Treasury secretariat buys out as part of an auction, they will collect an extra tax on the gold parachute, unless the discretionary bank president retires.
Immediately after the acquisition of suspicious receivables, the government will act aggressively to ensure that the amount paid to leaders is not exaggerated.
In order for the image to be complete, it is nevertheless necessary to add that the existing golden parachutes are not modified. The ceiling only concerns new contracts, this in order to motivate participation in the plan.
It is the first time in the history of the United States that legal ceilings will be in force for the appointments of directors general - commented the chairman of the committee responsible for the financial benefits of the House of Deputies, the Democrat Barney Frank.
In addition, the State acquires a right to acquire shares in the banks participating in the plan, thus reducing the risk of taxpayers, since they can even be a winner in the business as soon as the economy and with it the saved banks fall back on their feet.
